                                       Description

Detects the use of encoded PowerShell commands, which are commonly used by attackers to hide malicious activity.


                                     Detection Logic

If PowerShell is executed with encoded command parameters such as "-enc" or "-EncodedCommand", it may indicate an attempt to obfuscate malicious scripts.


                                       Splunk Query

index=windows process="powershell.exe"
| where like(CommandLine, "%-enc%") OR like(CommandLine, "%EncodedCommand%")



                                       Example Scenario

A user downloads a malicious file that executes a hidden PowerShell command using encoding to avoid detection. This command may download malware or establish a connection to an external server.


                                             Response Actions

- Investigate the full command line execution
- Decode the Base64 command if possible
- Identify any external connections
- Isolate the affected machine if malicious activity is confirmed
- Check for persistence mechanisms
